Part 1 (multi-thread) is stored in the folder labeled "Part 1". Part 2 (multi-process) is stored in the folder labeled "Part 2". These instructions can be used for both parts.

Type make to build the executable, produce.

Type make clean to remove all files, but the original C files

To run produce, type in ./produce 20 2 1 3 , where 20 is the number of messages to be sent, 2 is the message queue size, 1 is the number of producers to create, 3 is the number of consumers to create. The message queue size has a maximum size of 10 in Part 2. Timing stats along with the integers consumed will be displayed.